to A Cook from CO; normal or "old-fashioned" peanut butter will separate oil from peanuts especially in heat. That's why I put my PB in the fridge after mixing it. processed peanut butter contains a hydrogenated fat which keeps the fat and rest of peanut paste from separating. Unfortunately, hydrogenated oil is extremely unhealthy. It is trans fat, the stuff that clogs arteries and makes heart disease. Just something to think about

