Interesting this is exactly the recipe (with some minor tweaks) I developed after experimenting and have been using for years to make chewy pb cookies. The tweaks use only brown sugar and decrease it to about 1 3/4 cups. Use margarine instead of butter and increase the baking powder by 1 more tsp. Cook for about 8 minutes at 350 in a convection oven. Oh and forget the parchment paper but it does help them to hold their shape if you let them cool on the rack for a few minutes. You won't be able to stop eating them!

